18 6 27 1166 ``I cannot emphasize enough how traumatic this would have been for the people in there to see one of their co-workers gunned down, so we're going to do all we can to help these people though a very, very difficult time,'' Const. Fanning said.
18 6 28 1167 Police were called immediately and surrounded the building, Const. Fanning said.
18 6 29 1168 ``We determined that there was nobody else in the building, just our victim, who was deceased, and the suspect,'' Const. Fanning said.
18 6 30 1169 What followed was a tense two hours while police negotiated with a suspect to give himself up.
18 6 31 1170 It's not known what kind of firearm was involved.
18 6 32 1171 Luke Pigeon, who lives in an apartment building next door, said he didn't hear a gunshot but was drawn to his window by a commotion outside.
18 6 33 1172 ``It wasn't typical, crazy noise that sometimes happens.
18 6 34 1173 You got the feeling there was something definitely, definitely wrong,'' Mr. Pigeon told The Canadian Press.
18 6 35 1174 He looked out the window and saw a woman fleeing the building next door.
18 6 36 1175 ``All I saw was a ... lady running down the block screaming,'' Mr. Pigeon said.
18 6 37 1176 He said she ran into the auto repair shop and in what seemed like mere minutes, police were on the scene.
18 6 38 1177 ``All of a sudden, in my front yard there were five totally decked out, geared up riot squad officers with guns out of the holster, aiming at the second floor of the building right beside us,'' Mr. Pigeon said.
18 6 39 1178 ``I tried to open up my door and they said 'close your door, lock your door.'''
18 6 40 1179 He spent the next two hours in his apartment, as police negotiated and finally persuaded a suspect to surrender.
18 6 41 1180 ``They cuffed him on the ground and they took him into a cruiser,'' Mr. Pigeon said.
18 6 42 1181 ``He was giving them a bit of grief, he was saying that his cuffs hurt, but he was following orders.''
18 6 43 1182 Mr. Pigeon also commended police for their handling of the dangerous situation.
18 6 44 1183 ``They managed to stop any further loss of life.''
18 6 45 1184 Mark Pinder was working at a film studio across the street when a police officer banged at his window.
18 6 46 1185 ``I didn't realize it was a police officer right away because he was a plainclothes officer,'' Mr. Pinder said.
18 6 47 1186 ``But then I saw that he had a weapon drawn.''
18 6 48 1187 The officer told Mr. Pinder to get everyone in the basement.
18 6 49 1188 Mr. Pinder and his fellow employees were just about to begin a party to celebrate the completion of a show they'd been working on.
18 6 50 1189 ``People grabbed a couple of bowls of chips and dip and we just sort of moved the party downstairs,'' Mr. Pinder said.
18 6 51 1190 ``Some people seemed quite concerned but there wasn't anyone freaking out or crying,'' Mr. Pinder said.
18 6 52 1191 ``Everyone was calling their family and making sure that people knew that they were okay.''
18 6 53 1192 Work place killings are rare, police say.
18 6 54 1193 ``It's something no business can prepare for,'' Const. Fanning said.
