30 12 5 3370 Three cable systems carrying more than 75 percent of traffic between the Middle East, Europe and America have been <MENTION CHAIN="2">damaged</MENTION>, according to the U.K.'s Interoute Plc, which operates a fiber- optic data network connecting 92 cities.
30 12 6 3371 The cables run from Alexandria in northern Egypt to Sicily in southern Italy.
30 12 7 3372 In January, an anchor severed the cables outside Alexandria after bad weather conditions forced ships to moor off the coast.
