30 7 12 3489 The French firm said it was sending a ship out to fix the line between Italy and Egypt, although it could take until 31 December to fully repair the line.
30 7 13 3490 The main damage is to the four submarine cables running across the Mediterranean and through the Suez Canal.
30 7 14 3491 It is thought that 65% of traffic to India was down, while services to Singapore, Malaysia, Saudi Arabia, Egypt, Taiwan and Pakistan have also been severely affected.
30 7 15 3492 Earlier this year, the same line was damaged in the same area - off the Egyptian coast - although only two lines were snapped then.
30 7 16 3493 ``We've lost three out of four lines.
30 7 17 3494 If the fourth cable breaks, we're looking at a total blackout in the Middle East,'' said Mr Wright.
30 7 18 3495 ``These three circuits account for 90% of the traffic and we're going to see more international phone calls dropping and a huge degradation in the quality of local internet,'' he added.
30 7 19 3496 ``Normally you would expect to see one major break per cable per year.
30 7 20 3497 With four you should have an insurance policy.
30 7 21 3498 For this to happen twice in one year, on the same cable, is a serious cause for concern.''
