44 3 5 5796 Hurd has relentlessly cut costs while demanding better execution from the company's remaining workers. 
44 3 6 5797 Meanwhile, HP has recovered from a nagging financial hangover that was exacerbated by the biggest acquisition in its 69-year history -- the $19 billion purchase of Compaq Computer, completed in 2002 over strident shareholder objections.
44 3 7 5798 Hewlett-Packard's <MENTION CHAIN="1">purchase</MENTION> of Electronic Data Systems could mean tougher competition for IBM and its 10,500 Triangle employees.
