7 1 1 6199 Wladimir Klitschko (52-3, 46 KOs) <MENTION CHAIN="1">blasted</MENTION> a sluggish Hasim Rahman (45-7-2, 36 KOs) in Mannheim, Germany on Saturday night to <MENTION CHAIN="2">retain</MENTION> the IBF, WBO and IBO world heavyweight titles.
7 1 2 6200 After flooring Rahman in the sixth round with a left-right combo Klitschko wasted little time wrapping it up in the seventh with a big left-right-left series that led to the referee stepping in and stopping the fight at the 2:15 mark.
7 1 3 6201 Rahman, a former heavyweight champion who shocked the world when he floored Lennox Lewis in 2001 for the title, showed absolutely no signs of life against Kiltschko on Saturday.
7 1 4 6202 The final numbers showed Klitschko landing 178 of 369 punches thrown while Rahman connected on just 30 of 207 punches thrown.
7 10 1 6203 Wladimir Klitschko <MENTION CHAIN="1">defended</MENTION> his IBF heavyweight crown by <MENTION CHAIN="1">stopping</MENTION> Hasim Rahman in the seventh round at SAP Arena on Saturday.
7 10 2 6204 Klitschko, who has not lost in more than four years, hit the shorter Rahman at will throughout, and after landing a left-right-left combination against the cornered American, the referee stepped in to end the contest. Rahman didn't appear upset.
7 10 3 6205 Klitschko had knocked down Rahman in the previous round with successive left hooks.
7 10 4 6206 The technical knockout in Klitchsko's sixth defense of the IBF belt - and third this year - improved the Ukrainian-born fighter to 52-3 with 46 KOs.
7 10 5 6207 Rahman, the two-time heavyweight champion who stepped in as a replacement opponent last month, struggled to get inside the taller Klitschko's reach, and dropped to 45-7-2.
7 10 6 6208 The fighters started out fast and light on their feet, but it soon became apparent that Rahman was struggling to overcome the 3 1/2-inch height advantage enjoyed by the champion.
7 10 7 6209 Rahman had to lean in drastically, and Klitschko easily fended off his punches.
7 10 8 6210 Rahman did little more than lean on the ropes for a time and guard his face as Klitschko sought his opening.
7 10 9 6211 Rahman looked reinvigorated in the fourth round, using his whole torso to make ambitious attacks, often connecting with Klitschko's body.
7 10 10 6212 But he rarely landed blows above Klitschko's shoulders, and the consequences were clear when Klitschko dropped Rahman early in the sixth with two hard lefts to the side of his head.
7 10 11 6213 Rahman got up but spent the remainder of the round in the corner, taking a sustained beating.
7 10 12 6214 Another flurry at the opening of the seventh ended Rahman's challenge.
7 10 13 6215 Klitschko also retained the minor WBO and IBO belts.
7 10 14 6216 Klitschko was originally scheduled to face Alexander Povetkin (16-0), but the Russian pulled out with an ankle injury.
7 10 15 6217 Rahman, who won the WBC and IBF belts from Lennox Lewis in 2001 and the vacant WBC belt in 2005, arrived in Germany on Monday and declared he was in top shape.
7 10 16 6218 On the undercard, former heavyweight champion Riddick Bowe made a modest comeback with an eighth-round decision over Germany's Gene Pukall.
7 10 17 6219 It was just the third fight in a decade for the 41-year-old American and his first in three years.
7 10 18 6220 Bowe (45-1, 33 KOs) had been training in Germany since September in an effort to get his stamina up and his weight down.
7 10 19 6221 The work paid off in the ring, where he kept up with the 33-year-old Pukall (14-13-2, 12KOs) and bested him with a stream of careful head shots.
