7 11 2 6223 The 32-year-old Klitschko (52-3, 46 KOs) <MENTION CHAIN="1">won</MENTION> his 10th consecutive <MENTION CHAIN="1">bout</MENTION> by <MENTION CHAIN="4">flooring</MENTION> Rahman (45-7-2) once before referee Tony Weeks <MENTION CHAIN="6">stopped</MENTION> the fight 44 seconds into the seventh round.
7 11 3 6224 In a fight that was one-sided from the start, Klitschko retained his IBF, WBO and IBO versions of the heavyweight crown. 
7 11 4 6225 Klitschko, who was coming off an 11th-round knockout of Tony Thompson in July, landed 178 punches to just 30 for Rahman.
7 11 5 6226 Klitschko used his jab to his advantage, scoring consistently, and by the sixth round the 36-year-old Rahman, a former heavyweight champion, looked tired and clearly beaten.
7 11 6 6227 In the sixth Klitschko landed a pair of left hooks to floor an off-balanced Rahman, who spent most of his time during the round on the ropes.
7 11 7 6228 In fact, Klitschko landed 28 of his 68 punches thrown during the round, while Rahman connected on just 1-of-16 over those three minutes.
