7 3 18 6253 The fact is that he shouldn't be in the ring at all but this is boxing and I'm sure that the former champion needs the money and that is why he is risking his life.
7 4 1 6254 Ukraine's Wladimir Klitschko retained his WBO, IBF and IBO world heavyweight titles on Saturday with a technical knockout of Hasim Rahman in round seven.
7 4 2 6255 The referee stopped the fight after Klitschko, 32, landed a series of punches to Rahman's head and the American retreated to the ropes, barely able to stand.
7 4 3 6256 The Ukrainian had already knocked him down in round six.
7 4 4 6257 ``I thought I could land some punches earlier but it wasn't worth it because Hasim Rahman knew he was up against the best and he was really focused, you could see that,'' said Klitschko, who has been dubbed 'Dr. Steelhammer'.
7 4 5 6258 ``He really hung in there and it wasn't easy,'' he added after improving his record to 52 wins and three defeats.
7 4 6 6259 Rahman was unable to get past Klitschko's left jab to land the kind of big punch that saw him beat world champion Lennox Lewis in 2001, when he knocked out the Briton with a right hook to record one of the biggest upsets in boxing history.
7 4 7 6260 Rahman, 36, had never really regained that form.
7 4 8 6261 He replaced Alexander Povetkin as Klitschko's opponent in October after the Russian pulled out of the bout with a foot injury.
7 4 9 6262 In the first two rounds, Klitschko, brother of WBC champion Vitali, used his left jab to good effect, producing fast combinations and landing punches to the head.
